						<summary>Ethical writings.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he"/>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="1r" to="142v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Sefer ma῾alot ha-midot</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">ספר
מעלות המדות</title>
							<author>
								<persName xml:lang="en" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/142650436">Anav, Jehiel ben Jekuthiel ben Benjamin, active 13th century</persName>
								<persName xml:lang="he" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/142650436">יחיאל בן יקותיאל, הרופא</persName>
							</author>
							<listBibl>
								<bibl>
									<ref target="Anav_1556"/>
								</bibl>
							</listBibl>
							<colophon xml:lang="he">אני <name type="person" role="author">יחיאל ביר' יקותיאל ביר' בנימן הרופא</name> נבתוי"א כתבתי זה הספר לבעל בריתי ר' <name type="person" role="patron">שלמה ביר' משה ביר' יוסף</name> נ"ע הרחמן יזכהו להגות בו הוא וזרעו וזרע זרעו עד סוף כל הדורות ויזכהו לקיים כל הכתוב בו אמן ונשלם באב של שנת <date calendar="Hebrew">מ"ז</date> לפרט.<locus n="142v"/>
							</colophon>
							<note>
								<p>A codicological comparison with other manuscripts written by Jehiel ben Jekuthiel shows that this manuscript is an autograph, a clean copy of his work written for Shelomoh ben Mosheh ben Yosef. See also <ref target="Feintuch_1985" type="page">51</ref>.</p>
							</note>
							<decoNote type="border">2 partial foliate borders inhabited by birds, in colours and gold. <locus from="1v" to="2r"/>
							</decoNote>
							<decoNote type="border">25 foliate scrolls around chapter titles and at the end, often inhabited by birds or dragons. <locus n="4r, 14v, 20r, 27r, 33r, 37r, 44r, 48v, 56r, 61r, 63v, 70v, 78v, 82r, 85r, 94r, 98r, 104v, 107r, 111v, 116r, 122r, 133r, 141r, 142v"/>
							</decoNote>
							<decoNote type="initial">1 chapter title accompanied by dragons.<locus n="76r"/>
							</decoNote>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="143r" to="145v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Sha῾ar ῾Ets Ḥayim</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">שער עץ חיים</title>
							<note>
								<p>A fragment only.</p>
							</note>
							<author>
								<persName xml:lang="en" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/39323094">Binyamin, min ha-ʻAnaṿim, 1215-1295</persName>
								<persName xml:lang="he" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/39323094">מן הענווים, בנימין</persName>
							</author>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Parchment codex of the 13th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="perg">
								<support>Parchment.</support>
								<extent>145 folios<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>145</height>
										<width>160</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>190/185</height>
										<width>105/100</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>145 folios (+ 3 unfoliated modern paper flyleaves and 1 older paper flyleaf at the beginning and at the end), folio 145 is a foliated parchment flyleaf. </p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>15 quires: i-xiii10 (folios 1-130), xiv8 (folios 131-138), xv6 (folios 139-144).</p>
								</collation>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1" ruledLines="31" writtenLines="31">
									<p>Uniform layout.</p>
									<p>Initial words in larger square characters.</p>
									<p>Edges are coloured red and black. </p>
									<p>Ruling is visible. </p>
									<p>Numerous maniculae.
</p>
									<p>Watermark, folio [iv] of three crescents, similar to <ref target="Heawood_1950" type="number">874</ref>, but without inscription (Venice, 1783).
</p>
									<p>Watermark, folio [146] of a letter V, unidentified.
</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>Italian semi-cursive script, unpunctuated, of the 13th century. <name type="person" role="scribe">Jehiel ben Jekuthiel ben Benjamin ha-Rofe</name>: inscribed with his name in the author's colophon, month Av [50]47 [<date calendar="Gregorian">1287</date>] (folio 141r).</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole"/>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="patron">Shelomoh ben Mosheh ben Yosef</name>: inscribed with his name in the author's colophon (folio 141r).
</p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="owner">Perets ben Menaḥem</name> sold to <name type="person" role="owner">Eli῾ezer ben Avraham</name>: inscribed with his name in a purchase note (14th century) (folio 1r).
</p>
							<p>Purchase note, mostly illegible (folio 1r).
</p>
							<p>Acquisition note, partially illegible (folio 1r).
</p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="owner">Shelomoh ben Yekutiel ben Shelomoh</name>: inscribed with his name (16th century) (folios 144v, 145r).</p>
							<p>Recipe for making ink (folio 145r).</p>
						</additions>
						<bindingDesc>
							<binding>
								<p>BM in-house.</p>
								<p>Spine: 'Jechiel ben Jekuthiel. Ma'aloth Ham-Middoth. Hebrew. Brit. Mus. Additional 26,974.'</p>
							</binding>
						</bindingDesc>
